The paper deals with entropy and information theory, which is a subfield of computer science. Specifically, it focuses on the entropy power of discrete random variables, which is a topic within information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves some optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the use of perturbed random variables and continuous entropy power inequality could relate to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
